  ],
  "purpose": "Convert the Phase 17 real-storage migration gate for persistence schema and audit logging into an executable validation contract before any real server database, schema migration, or audit-log runtime exists. Phase 18 defines planned schema surfaces, per-table minimum fields, audit event shape, dry-run migration rules, deletion/export audit obligations, profile isolation, replay rules, capability boundaries, migration gates, and side-effect truth.",
  "nonGoals": [
    "No runtime implementation.",
    "No real server process.",
    "No network listener or network request.",
    "No database opened.",
    "No database created.",
    "No database or source-store write.",
    "No file write.",
    "No migration executed.",
    "No queue creation or enqueue.",
    "No auth, secret, token, or session change.",
    "No local execution.",
    "No shell or PTY action.",
    "No browser, window, screenshot, or OCR access.",
    "No external sends or customer sends.",
    "No deploys.",
    "No trades or financial actions.",
    "No memory or profile commits.",
    "No export file written.",
    "No deletion performed.",
    "No restore performed.",
    "No raw content stored."
  ],
  "builderPatchMustSatisfy": {
    "scope": [
      "Build validation-only persistence-schema/audit-log assessment records against this fixture, if Builder is later delegated.",
      "Do not start a server, open/create/write a database, run migrations, write files, perform network work, create queues, mutate auth/session/token state, execute locally, send, deploy, trade, commit memory/profile state, export a file, delete records, restore records, or store raw content.",
      "Represent commit afabea1 as the Phase 17 baseline and preserve storage/deletion/export/retention as validation-only gates.",
      "Emit persistence_assessment, allowed_schema_surfaces, forbidden_schema_surfaces, per_table_minimum_fields, audit_event_contract, migration_plan_rules, deletion_export_audit_rules, profile_isolation_replay_rules, capability_boundary, migration_gates, gate summary, blocker summary, evidence refs, and side-effect truth sections.",
      "Define only planned validation schema surfaces; do not create tables, indexes, migrations, files, or databases.",
      "Make audit events append-only, scoped, redacted, monotonic, and free of raw payloads.",
      "Treat schema/audit validity as planning validation only, never as authorization for execution, external side effects, durable memory/profile commits, raw restore, or resurrection of deleted state."
    ],
    "hardRejects": [
      "Any server process, network request/listener, database open/create/write, source-store write, file write, migration execution, queue write, auth/secret/token/session change, local execution, shell/PTY, browser/window access, send, customer send, deploy, trade, financial action, durable migration, memory/profile commit, export-file write, deletion, restore, or raw-content storage occurs.",
      "Any fixture or validation output creates or implies live schema tables, indexes, migrations, files, queues, or database records.",
      "Any schema surface permits raw comms bodies, raw terminal scrollback, OCR/screenshot/browser DOM/cookies, customer private content, secrets/tokens/private keys, side-profile payloads in main, command bodies, irreversible send/deploy/trade execution records, or raw database payloads.",
      "Audit events include raw payloads, raw before/after content, raw deleted content, token values, private keys, command bodies, browser state, customer private content, or side-profile content.",
      "Duplicate idempotency keys are accepted silently, watermarks regress, tombstones lose to stale uploads, or deleted local memory/profile state can be resurrected by server restore.",
      "Schema or audit validity is treated as authorization for local execution, shell/PTY, Builder/Oracle direct targeting, Tier 2+ work, customer sends, deploys, trades, memory/profile commits, bridge green, model-processing proof, raw restore, or resurrection of deleted local state.",
      "Phase 18 migration language implies a real DB can exist before DB engine choice, encryption/key-reference policy, backup retention policy, audit viewer/operator controls, deletion/export API, migration runner safety, schema compatibility tests, disaster recovery plan, and profile isolation integration tests are reviewed."
    ]
  },
